Summarized Financial Data – Chevron U.S.A. Inc.
Chevron U.S.A. Inc. (CUSA) is a major subsidiary of Chevron Corporation. CUSA and its subsidiaries manage and operate most of
Chevron’s U.S. businesses. Assets include those related to the exploration and production of crude oil, natural gas and natural gas
liquids and those associated with the refining, marketing, supply and distribution of products derived from petroleum, excluding
most of the regulated pipeline operations of Chevron. CUSA also holds the company’s investment in the Chevron Phillips
Chemical Company LLC joint venture, which is accounted for using the equity method. The summarized financial information for
